messages.content: Don't make assumptions about what values to plug into functions. Ask for clarification if a user request is ambiguous.
It looks like your device’s location service is currently turned off, so I can’t determine your position. Would you like me to enable location services now?
Sure, go ahead and turn it on.

messages.name: setting_6
messages.content: PermissionError: Location service cannot be turned on in low battery mode

Your device is currently in Low Battery Mode, which is preventing location services from being enabled. Would you like me to disable Low Battery Mode so I can turn on Location Services? Once Location is on, I’ll just need your current latitude and longitude to look up your address.
Yeah, please disable the Low Battery Mode so we can proceed.
Low Battery Mode is now off and Location Services have been enabled. Please share your current latitude and longitude, and I’ll look up your address for you.
I don't know my latitude and longitude.

No problem. Here’s how you can find your latitude and longitude:

1. On a smartphone  
   • Open Google Maps (or Apple Maps).  
   • Tap and hold on your current blue “dot” until a pin drops.  
   • The coordinates will appear in the search bar or in the pin details.

2. On a computer  
   • Go to maps.google.com.  
   • Right-click your current location on the map.  
   • Select “What’s here?”  
   • A card at the bottom will show your latitude and longitude.

Once you have those two numbers (for example: 37.421542, -122.085589), just paste them here and I’ll look up your address. Let me know if you need any help!
I'll check on Google Maps on my phone and let you know. Thanks.
Sounds good! Take your time finding the coordinates. Whenever you have your latitude and longitude, just send them over and I’ll look up your address right away.
